# Implementation Plan: Role Realignment, TV Layout Update, and Enhanced Analytics

This plan outlines the changes required to reorganize user roles (adding an `admin` role, updating `owner`, renaming `Front Desk` to `Assistant Staff` and enforcing its restrictions), separate Status and Location columns in the Daily Intakes table, adjust the TV monitoring layout, and enhance the Analytics and Search functionality.

## User Review Required

> [!IMPORTANT]
> - We are introducing a new **Admin** role that will handle staff creation/management and records access.
> - The **Owner** role will focus on branch-level analytics (Branch A & B) and records.
> - The **Assistant Staff** role (formerly Front Desk) will have almost all controls disabled in the table, except for changing the **Arrival** time.
> - The **Service Advisor (SA)** will have separated columns for Status and Location, and the Goal column will be renamed to a more professional tone (e.g., "Service SLA (2h)") and completely hidden for both Assistant Staff and SA roles.

> [!WARNING]
> Since we are adding a new `admin` role to the database, we need to update the Mongoose User model enum and update seed data so there is a default admin account. We will seed `admin@hontech.com` / `admin123` for this purpose.

